The ruling party, Georgian Dream, has been the main source of controversy and debate surrounding the election (1,3,4,7,8,10). Despite attempts to debunk claims of fraud by President Donald Trump and his supporters, state election officials maintain that the election was free of significant fraud (5). The new parliament, formed by the ruling party, has already held its first session (1). The ruling party plans to establish a commission of inquiry into the election (7). The fall session of the parliament is set to open soon, with a focus on approving the 2021 state budget (9).

Overview.Summary: The 2020 Georgian parliamentary election took place on October 31, 2020 (5, 7, 9, 10, 11, 12, 13, 19, 20). The ruling party, Georgian Dream, spent 4.3 million GEL on election commercials (9). The election was declared the winner for a third time by Joe Biden (3). The Black share of the electorate fell to its lowest level since 2006 (13). The coalition government was preferred by 70% of voters (11). The election was not flawless, according to international observers (5). The election results were rejected by opposition parties, leading to protests (6, 7, 17). The election also saw a rise in women elected to Parliament (16). The runoff election on January 5, 2021, will determine control of the Senate in the 117th Congress (4, 14). There were also parliamentary elections in Lithuania (12, 19) and Moldova (20) around the same time.
